



Sir,
Congress Chamber [Philadelphia] 19 Septr 1775



The Congress have sent to you by Major William Coates, & Captain Joseph Copperthwait five hundred twenty seven thousand four hundred and eighty dollars continental money to be delivered to the paymaster & subject to your Order for the use
[16]
of The Army under your Command.1 I have the honour to be, Sir Your most Obedt hum. servt

John Hancock President


The Cloathing is on the way.2 Your Letters are now under the Consideration of Congress, & you will soon hear from us. pray forward your plans for Winter &c. as soon as possible.

